WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.414
Open Operations, then Appointments.

p02
00:00:01.414 --> 00:00:06.202
This is the booking board customers land on, not the staff roster.

p03
00:00:06.202 --> 00:00:07.616
Shifts live somewhere else.

p04
00:00:07.616 --> 00:00:12.686
Here you are looking at the jobs people reserved: details, oil changes, inspections,

p05
00:00:12.686 --> 00:00:15.797
each pinned to a day and a time.

p06
00:00:16.240 --> 00:00:18.050
Start with the four numbers up top.

p07
00:00:18.537 --> 00:00:20.732
Eighteen today, eighty-four this week.

p08
00:00:21.429 --> 00:00:25.546
Utilization at seventy-eight percent tells you how full your capacity is running,

p09
00:00:26.055 --> 00:00:29.515
and the three percent no-show rate is the slice that never showed.

p10
00:00:30.148 --> 00:00:34.297
Read these first and you know how the week is going before opening a single row.

p11
00:00:34.720 --> 00:00:36.267
Next, the three panels. First one, Booking Trend.

p12
00:00:36.529 --> 00:00:38.095
It plots the last twelve months, eight hundred forty bookings, up nineteen percent.

p13
00:00:38.568 --> 00:00:43.255
One glance tells you whether volume is climbing or sliding,

p14
00:00:43.745 --> 00:00:49.517
which is the context every other number sits inside.

p15
00:00:49.920 --> 00:00:51.456
Middle panel, the service mix.

p16
00:00:51.456 --> 00:00:54.615
Full details lead, interior details next, then oil changes,

p17
00:00:54.615 --> 00:00:56.457
with everything else rolled into other.

p18
00:00:56.457 --> 00:00:59.056
This is what customers are actually booking,

p19
00:00:59.056 --> 00:01:03.663
and it is the mix your bays and your people have to be ready for.

p20
00:01:04.080 --> 00:01:05.921
Right panel, schedule health.

p21
00:01:06.611 --> 00:01:07.990
Most bookings are confirmed, a smaller share still pending, and a thin slice marked no-show.

p22
00:01:08.300 --> 00:01:12.187
Confirmed is locked in.

p23
00:01:12.675 --> 00:01:13.960
Pending still needs the customer to say yes.

p24
00:01:14.275 --> 00:01:16.566
Watch that middle band,

p25
00:01:16.896 --> 00:01:21.828
because a quick phone call there turns a maybe into a filled bay.

p26
00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:23.538
Now scroll to the list.

p27
00:01:23.957 --> 00:01:26.168
Eighteen records, one row per booking.

p28
00:01:26.737 --> 00:01:29.650
Up on the right, a small toggle: List or Calendar.

p29
00:01:30.018 --> 00:01:32.214
You are in List now, the row-by-row view.

p30
00:01:32.662 --> 00:01:35.804
We flip to Calendar shortly, but first walk the controls.

p31
00:01:36.306 --> 00:01:37.173
Two buttons here.

p32
00:01:37.570 --> 00:01:39.657
New Record starts a fresh booking, and Export downloads the list.

p33
00:01:39.918 --> 00:01:41.780
We touch neither today.

p34
00:01:42.120 --> 00:01:43.529
Export especially stays untouched while recording,

p35
00:01:43.918 --> 00:01:49.120
and the new-booking form is its own lesson.

p36
00:01:49.520 --> 00:01:51.250
Under the header, the search row.

p37
00:01:51.728 --> 00:01:55.058
Type into the box to narrow the list by a name or a service,

p38
00:01:55.424 --> 00:01:57.653
or open Filters to slice it by column.

p39
00:01:58.106 --> 00:02:02.234
Handy when a customer calls and you need their booking in seconds, not scrolling.

p40
00:02:02.694 --> 00:02:03.639
Look at the columns.

p41
00:02:03.921 --> 00:02:04.391
Date, time, customer, service, location, staff, and status.

p42
00:02:04.635 --> 00:02:05.113
Seven of them, each sortable, with a checkbox on every row.

p43
00:02:05.362 --> 00:02:19.680
One line carries the whole booking: when, who, what, where, who works it, and where it stands.

p44
00:02:20.138 --> 00:02:23.285
Run down the staff and status columns.

p45
00:02:23.285 --> 00:02:26.607
Right now staff reads to be determined on these bookings,

p46
00:02:26.607 --> 00:02:28.839
and status shows confirmed or scheduled.

p47
00:02:28.839 --> 00:02:30.536
That is the tell.

p48
00:02:30.536 --> 00:02:33.201
This board captures the booking first,

p49
00:02:33.201 --> 00:02:37.520
and who actually works it gets assigned separately, over on the team schedule.

p50
00:02:37.920 --> 00:02:39.780
Down at the foot, the pager.

p51
00:02:40.747 --> 00:02:42.486
Twenty-five rows to a page, arrows to move between them.

p52
00:02:42.797 --> 00:02:48.794
A small thing, but it keeps a busy week from turning into an endless scroll.

p53
00:02:49.200 --> 00:02:50.336
Now flip the view. Click Calendar.

p54
00:02:50.764 --> 00:02:51.744
The same bookings rearrange into a calendar.

p55
00:02:52.069 --> 00:02:54.527
Nothing gets booked, nothing moves.

p56
00:02:55.006 --> 00:02:57.034
It is purely a different way to look at the week,

p57
00:02:57.410 --> 00:03:03.132
which is the faster read when someone wants to shift a day around.

p58
00:03:03.600 --> 00:03:05.270
Click List to come back.

p59
00:03:06.080 --> 00:03:08.605
The table returns exactly as it was.

p60
00:03:09.693 --> 00:03:12.114
The toggle is a lens, not a change.

p61
00:03:12.736 --> 00:03:15.920
Flip it as often as you like without touching a record.

p62
00:03:16.320 --> 00:03:18.591
One more look, the sidebar.

p63
00:03:18.591 --> 00:03:22.674
Under Appointments sit its neighbors: schedulable services, resources, business hours,

p64
00:03:22.674 --> 00:03:24.307
messaging, payments, and reports.

p65
00:03:24.307 --> 00:03:29.533
Each is its own workspace, and each is its own lesson.

p66
00:03:29.533 --> 00:03:32.364
We name them and move on.

p67
00:03:32.364 --> 00:03:37.412
Messaging sends real customer notices, so we leave it closed.

p68
00:03:37.840 --> 00:03:39.389
So that is Appointments.

p69
00:03:39.861 --> 00:03:41.744
Numbers up top for the pulse of the day,

p70
00:03:42.060 --> 00:03:43.472
panels for the mix and the health,

p71
00:03:43.913 --> 00:03:48.731
a list for the individual bookings,

p72
00:03:49.586 --> 00:03:50.843
and a toggle to read it as rows or as a week.

p73
00:03:51.262 --> 00:03:54.541
Keep one line straight: bookings live here, shifts live on the team schedule.

p74
00:03:55.063 --> 00:03:58.055
Learn this page and every scheduling call gets shorter.

